{
  "texts": [
    "1 Eta-squared (η 2) is a measure of effect size for use in ANOVA (Analysis of variance).",
    "It is analogous to R 2 from multiple linear regression.",
    "The eta-square effect sizes are interpreted usually as follows: η 2 = 0.01 indicates a small effect.",
    "η 2 = 0.06 indicates a medium effect.",
    "η 2 = 0.14 indicates a large effect."
  ]
}